<br>
Well its not.<br>
<br>
I understand that with the hand-me-down armor and the free weapons that I am pretty bare bones. No magic items, no spell crafted armor etc etc, but still. I found blues to be a challenge and yellows down-right impossible to solo in DF.<br>
<br>
Plated feinds and Lilispawns would force me to sit and sit and sit while I regenerated health.<br>
<br>
I am a 30 Firby BM with 30 in blunt, and 29 in DW. Is taking so much damage the norm or can I simply account for it because of the cheap free armor and weapons?<br>
<br>
ANyone? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dork of the Month~!</span><br>  Posts: 570<br> <font color=#000000>(7/22/03 6:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arg do Blademasters Suck or Something?</span><hr size=1> Ummm, crap equipment (hurts a LOT more than you think) combined with no spec in parry and crap dex/quick (thus crappy evade) = whole lotta sitting.  Hate to point out the obvious, but at least until you get decent equipment you're gonna have to go way out of your way to get into groups to xp remotely efficiently. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
